place.name: ANWICK
place.gazetteerText: ANWICK, a parish in Sleaford district, Lincoln; near the Sleaford canal, 4½ miles ENE of Sleaford r. station. Post Town, Sleaford. Acres, 1,820. Real property, £2,773. Pop., 277. Houses, 58. The property is divided among a few. The living is a vicarage annexed to the rectory of Branncewell, in the diocese of Lincoln. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
